quest_title: The numerical ratio of displacement to the distance covered is always
explanation_txt:
Distance is the length of path travelled by a body in a certain interval of time.

Displacement is the shortest distance between two end points of the path travelled by the body.

\(\therefore\)Displacement is always less than or equal to distance, but never greater than distance. Hence numerical ratio of displacement to the distance covered is always equal to or less than one.

quest_title: 100ml of 0.4N-HCl is mixed with 100ml of 0.6N of \(\text{H\({}_{2}\)SO\({}_{4}\).}\) What is the normality of the resulting solution?
explanation_txt:
100 ml of 0.4N HCl = 40 ml of 1N HCl

100 ml of 0.6N \(H_2SO_4\) = 60 ml of 1N \(H_2SO_4\)

Equivalent addition = 100 ml of 1N acid

Since the total volume of solution after the addition of individual acids is 200 ml, so 100 ml of 1N acid = 200 ml of 0.5N acid.

Hence, the normality of the solution is 0.5N.

quest_title: Which one below is a pseudohalide ?
explanation_txt:
Pseudohalide ions and Pseudohalogens

There are certain monovalent negative ions made up of two or more electronegative atoms which exhibit properties similar to these of halide ions. Such ions are known as pseudo halide ions just as halide ions, pseudo halide ions have also corresponding dimoric molecules. These are called pseudo halogens and show properties similar to those of halogens

quest_title: When 100 volts dc is applied across a solenoid a current of 1.0 amp flows in it. When 100 volts ac is applied across it, the current drops to 0.5 amp. If the frequency of the ac source is 50 Hz, the impedance and inductance of the solenoid are
explanation_txt:
In case of \(\mathrm{DC}, \omega=0,\) and hence, \(Z=R\)
\(Z=R=\cfrac{V}{I}=\cfrac{100}{1}=100 \Omega\)
For \(\mathrm{AC}, \quad Z=\sqrt{R^{2}+(2 \pi f L)^{2}}\)
And \(Z=\cfrac{100}{0.5}=200 \Omega\)
\(\Rightarrow 200=\sqrt{100^{2}+(100 \pi L)^{2}}\)
\(\therefore L=0.55 \mathrm{H}\)
